{
  "texts": [
    "-Inductive Transfer Learning, where labelled data is available in both the source and target domains, and the source and target tasks are different.",
    "The focus is not on domain differences but rather on leveraging labelled data from the source domain to improve learning in the target domain.",
    "-Transductive Transfer Learning, where, the source and target domains are different, but they share the same task.",
    "However, labelled data is only available for the source domain.",
    "The objective is to employ the labelled data from the source domain to enhance learning in the target domain."
  ]
}